snippet.textDisplay:
I need some Koreans to see this and you might hate me for it:

There's a lot of theft going on in the music you export to your global, young fans. Who can tell? Your global drama fans who are also music enthusiasts can tell if they are millenials and on. 

That's the secret to your fast production of music. Your composers steal a line's worth of melody in most of the famous songs and sometimes there is more than one line from famous artists. 

Maybe it's not theft when the stolen melody is that short, but what they are doing is not adding to music, it's basically creating a combination of already existing music. 

This will run its course and music will globally eat itself up if you keep walking this already much beaten path. 

Also, the time in between causes the younger generations to lose the chance to compare the quality of older music to newer music. 


Music is much more than that created by algorithms, robots and sht that choose melodies from a pool, clip and paste them according to certain rules of music that are known to please the human ear. You've also been rendering music impersonal by agreeing to pander to this. 

No one can stop the Korean wave if you stopped support-streaming music that you find shtty, mundane, of low quality and impersonal just because some guy or girl whose looks makes you go wet sings to it. In fact Korean music could only be here to stay if you stopped doing that and let your other, true musicians break through the mold to reach over and around. 

You have so many creative musicians that could help you do that. Here we've all listened to one of them.

snippet.textDisplay: I have been listening to him and other K-indie forever, as well as J-rock, J-metal, and other classic rock, pop, indie (from 40s to modern), jazz, some, Asian, South America, and some other countries traditional works and their versions of indie, rock, metal, etcetera (by others, I mean what wouldn't first come to mind like Europe, America, East Asia and other countries near by like Thialand and the Philippines, Australia, Native American/Indigenous People, etcetera, but I have also found great things to come out of some of these genres from Mongolia, India, some countries in Africa, etcetera that at first you may not expect to produce great metal, rock, indie, etcetera mentioned.) However, you'd be quite surprised at the music that comes out of some of them if you are searching for more and didn't consider them and they haven't popped up as "crossover recommendations" when you select the music variants you prefer! Sadly, with my account being over 10 years old and my "childish" habits of not downsizing as a girl and just adding random stuff on a whim I noticed YouTube over time added and deleted random things on it's own over time (possibly "glitches" *chuckles*, we all know that probably weren't "glitches") and so a lot of my playlists that were made several years ago have disappeared and I even discovered random K-pop, Vocaloid, EDM, etcetera in my lists that I don't really listen to! Note: in my youth I used to be slightly more "goth" and listen to a lot of classic darkwave and similar music like Souxie and the Banchees and a band I stopped listeng to a while back as they started to go quickly into a synth pop/clubish style/overly remixed direction as they tried to stay independent and completely self-produce and thus had a lot of B.S. from artists, labels, etcetera trying to claim it was theirs as they were more established and thus they moved to remixing some of their old and new stuff more; which was why I left them. Also, I am a nerd and into silly, comedic, parody type bands like Voltaire. I do not typically like to mention other artists on random pages after dealing with getting dragged randomly into all the inter-group, pointless fighting on K-pop pages, that happens on some of the groups of the various groups I listen to, etcetera! I typically just like to relax and listen! However, my coments/message area thing on my page is always open if you want to ask for suggestions as I love spreading new music and other interestings with people in a more "controlled setting" that does not hopefully directly impact the content creators themselves! So, if you would like to find some new music and other content, please don't hesitate to stop by my page! Tale care and be safe everyone!

HYUKOH - WI ING WI ING (English Translation)

My legs that totter along as I walk
I spent another day that slipped away without any meaning
I believe that people can only love in groups
But there's rarely a reason for me to anxiously take part in that.

Whirl, whirl, a day in a life
Flies far away as if it's laughing at me.
Spin, spin, spinning around,
This world it trembles as if it's laughing at me.

Tell me, tell me, please don't tell,
It would be better for me if I wasn't able to hear.
Tell me, tell me, please don't tell,
It would be better for me if I wasn't able to see.

Ai ai ai ai ai ai
Ai ai ai ai ai ai
Ai ai ai ai ai ai
Ai ai ai ai ai ai

During morning rush hour at the station where it's full of people,
There's no reason for someone like me to use a subway pass.
I stumble round and round at home with nothing better to do.
I'm really overwhelmed with guilt at how pathetic I am.

Whirl, whirl, a day in a life,
Flies far away as if it's laughing at me.
Spin, spin, spinning around,
This world it trembles as if it's laughing at me.

Can't do anything against my scarred and callused old heart.
